ORF467 | Transportation Systems Analysis | http://registrar.princeton.edu/course-offerings/course_details.xml?courseid=008008&term=1162 | instructors:Alain L. Kornhauser description:Studied is the transportation sector of the economy from a technology  and policy planning perspective.  The focus is on the methodologies and analytical tools that underpin policy formulation, capital and operations planning, and real-time operational decision making within the transportation industry. Case studies of innovative concepts such as "value" pricing,  real-time fleet management and control, GPS-based route guidance systems, automated transit systems and autonomous vehicles will provide a practical focus for the methodologies.  Class project in lieu of final exam focused on major issue in Transportation Systems Analysis.
